27:23.726 --> 27:26.468
Sounds like he’s not alone.
I’ll—I’ll get the door.

27:26.562 --> 27:27.642
[ Muffled Groan ]
Shh.

27:27.730 --> 27:28.685
[ Muffled Whimper]

27:28.773 --> 27:30.889
[Whimpering]

27:30.983 --> 27:32.644
[ Muffled Shouting ]

27:32.735 --> 27:35.192
Drop it, Reese!
Drop it.

27:35.279 --> 27:37.895
Just give me an excuse.
Just one.

27:39.450 --> 27:41.361
[ Knife Clatters On Floor]

27:48.376 --> 27:50.617
[ Sweets ]
You know, most doctors
live by a code of ethics.

27:50.711 --> 27:52.622
“Do no harm” is one of them.

27:52.713 --> 27:56.581
And who was I harming,
Dr. Sweets?
I’m the victim here.

27:56.676 --> 27:58.166
You’re the—
Excuse me?

27:58.261 --> 28:01.424
You were caught tying up
a woman, holding a knife.

28:01.514 --> 28:03.220
Harmless role—play.

28:03.307 --> 28:06.299
And paying Jessica,
who was one of your patients,
that’s also harmless?

28:06.394 --> 28:07.304
Yes.

28:09.438 --> 28:13.727
I follow my passions.
That’s nothing to be ashamed of.

28:13.818 --> 28:17.652
It’s moralizing psychologists
like you that make society
puritanical and narrow—minded.

28:17.738 --> 28:19.899
It’s psychologists like me
that understand that you are—

28:19.991 --> 28:23.609
to coin a 19th—century term
you might be familiar with—
a paraphiliac.

28:23.703 --> 28:29.073
I don’t want to kidnap
and ravish an actual
unwitting young woman.

28:29.166 --> 28:32.750
So I hire someone
to play the role
of the damsel in distress.

28:32.879 --> 28:35.586
That’s all these events were.
But even though
you were paying her,

28:35.673 --> 28:38.255
you still had to get Jessica
drunk to get her to play along.

28:38.342 --> 28:40.048
Jessica had never been
handcuffed before.

28:40.136 --> 28:42.969
She was nervous.
I was hoping that a Iibation
would loosen her up a little.

28:43.055 --> 28:45.137
Well, judging by the fractures
on her wrists,

28:45.224 --> 28:48.557
— I guess that didn’t work out too well, did it?
— Jessica began struggling.

28:48.644 --> 28:50.430
She was screaming
to be let go.

28:50.521 --> 28:53.979
Since you’re into bondage,
seeing her in pain must have
turned you on.

28:55.651 --> 28:57.437
I’m not a monster.

28:59.071 --> 29:02.984
Listen, that poor girl
was making herself bleed...

29:03.075 --> 29:05.407
trying to rip the handcuffs
from the bedpost.

29:05.494 --> 29:08.577
I took them off her
as quickly as I could.

29:08.664 --> 29:10.825
Next thing I know,
the front door is kicked in,

29:10.917 --> 29:14.000
this 250—pound behemoth
throws me across the room.

29:14.754 --> 29:16.415
Her pimp?
Bodyguard?

29:16.505 --> 29:18.120
He stuffed me in a closet.

29:18.257 --> 29:20.293
Did he say anything?
No!

29:20.384 --> 29:22.466
I mean,
he was obviously furious.

29:22.553 --> 29:24.339
But he was silent.
No threats, nothing.

29:27.725 --> 29:31.889
Well, we’ll be analyzing all
of the surgical instruments
from your clinic, Dr. Reese.

29:31.979 --> 29:33.560
Be my guest.

29:33.648 --> 29:36.481
And the antique medical
equipment we found hidden
in your apartment.

29:39.403 --> 29:41.985
Those tools
are very valuable.

29:42.073 --> 29:45.031
That’s the only reason
that they were hidden.

29:46.327 --> 29:47.612
[ Exhales ]

29:47.703 --> 29:49.785
These antiques are beautiful,

29:49.872 --> 29:53.490
but the edges are far too rough
to have caused
the injuries we found.

29:53.584 --> 29:56.951
If I were to create
a calendar of history’s
most ghoulish killings,

29:57.046 --> 29:59.332
the Black Dahlia murder
would have to be
my December.

29:59.423 --> 30:04.258
Had medical examiners in 1947
had access to the technology
we have today,

30:04.345 --> 30:06.711
Elizabeth Short’s murder
would have certainly
been solved.

30:06.847 --> 30:11.136
The medio—cam would have easily
unearthed particulates left
behind by the murder weapon.

30:11.227 --> 30:15.436
The considerable space
between the blade
and the “V”—shaped incision...

30:15.523 --> 30:19.107
suggests this knife
is too small to be
the murder weapon.

30:19.193 --> 30:21.479
But we’ve onlyjust begun.

30:21.570 --> 30:24.562
Sure looks like the doc
loved his sharp objects.

30:24.657 --> 30:28.650
And we have casts
of some of the bone injuries.

30:28.744 --> 30:33.033
Will you tell me again about
the French nobleman who bathed
in the blood of children?

30:33.165 --> 30:35.827
In a moment, Mr. Fisher.
Okay.

30:35.918 --> 30:39.536
Both knives appear to be tilted
downward in the femur...

30:39.630 --> 30:41.166
at the same 45—degree angle.

30:41.257 --> 30:45.626
And it looks like
a 45—degree angle
on the humerus...

30:45.720 --> 30:47.210
and the radius as well.

30:47.304 --> 30:51.138
All of these incisions
appear to have been made
in a downward motion...

30:51.267 --> 30:54.384
at precisely
the same angle.
Meaning?

30:54.478 --> 30:57.936
The killer was even more precise
than we had originally thought.

30:58.024 --> 31:00.811
Well, I can’t think of anyone
more precise than a doctor.

31:00.901 --> 31:02.892
I wish his tools
agreed with you.

31:08.701 --> 31:12.068
Hey, Booth, I wanted
to apologize for last night.

31:12.163 --> 31:15.200
I totally took advantage
of your hospitality.
That wasn’t cool.

31:15.291 --> 31:18.499
Uh, don’t worry about it,
Sweets. You know what?
It’s a— It’s a great tub.

31:18.627 --> 31:21.664
Oh, it really is.
Those jets are awesome.
Stop.

31:21.797 --> 31:23.879
All right, enough
with the tub talk.
Okay.

31:24.008 --> 31:25.999
[Cell Phone Rings]
Um, I’m looking
for an apartment.

31:26.135 --> 31:29.343
[Beeps]
That’s good. You know what?
That’s a great first step.

31:29.472 --> 31:31.212
Oh.
What is it?

31:31.307 --> 31:34.344
None of the doctor’s tools
match the injuries
of the bones.

31:34.435 --> 31:37.552
I gotta admit,
I’m off the doctor
as a prime suspect.

31:37.646 --> 31:39.511
So, what are you thinking?
It was the pimp?

31:39.607 --> 31:43.691
Well, I’m wondering why
a pimp would interrupt
his prostitute at work.

31:43.778 --> 31:46.440
[ Groans ]
She could be freelancing.

31:46.530 --> 31:48.987
Cutting the pimp out
of the equation. Yeah, that
could get someone killed.

31:49.116 --> 31:49.980
Or—
Or?

31:50.076 --> 31:51.987
The big guy was a client...

31:52.078 --> 31:53.739
who had developed
feelings for Jessica.

31:53.829 --> 31:56.036
You know, that kind
of paranoid, unrequited love...

31:56.123 --> 31:59.240
could definitely fuel
feelings of intense rage.

31:59.335 --> 32:01.826
That’s him.
That’s our guy.
I gotta find him.

32:02.546 --> 32:04.958
I gotta find an apartment.

32:07.676 --> 32:11.260
[Angela ]
Okay, so keep
your eye out for a man,

32:11.347 --> 32:13.053
approximately 6 foot 6,

32:13.140 --> 32:17.099
between 250 and 280 pounds,
dark hair.

32:17.186 --> 32:20.144
I am looking for him
anywhere near Reese’s place.

32:20.231 --> 32:21.721
[Saroyan ] I wouldn’t
imagine there would be...

32:21.816 --> 32:23.807
that many surveillance cameras
in the neighborhood.

32:23.901 --> 32:26.108
Yeah. You know,
none of the artisanal shops
even use them.

32:26.195 --> 32:27.901
Half of them
don’t even have phones.

32:27.988 --> 32:30.730
In New York, the police
eventually tracked down...

32:30.825 --> 32:32.531
the Son of Sam through
a parking ticket.

32:32.618 --> 32:35.781
A ticket. That’s genius, Cam.

32:35.871 --> 32:39.113
This Web site collects
all traffic violations...

32:39.208 --> 32:41.790
to analyze traffic flow
and congestion.

32:41.877 --> 32:45.870
— And?
- Reese lives one door
from the intersection.

32:45.965 --> 32:48.707
These are all the photos of
the drivers caught
running the red...

32:48.801 --> 32:52.419
on Reese’s block
on Saturday night
when Jessica was with Reese.

32:52.555 --> 32:54.341
You think
he was driving?
No, no.

32:54.431 --> 32:56.046
But look at the angle
of the camera.

32:56.142 --> 32:58.428
Right across the street
from Reese’s building.

33:00.521 --> 33:03.137
There he is.
Look, in the background.

33:03.232 --> 33:06.565
— You sure this is our guy?
— Well, yeah.

33:06.652 --> 33:09.985
I mean, unless you see another
6—foot—6, 250—pound man...

33:10.072 --> 33:12.939
in front of Reese’s building
at the same time
the victim was there.

33:13.033 --> 33:16.321
Let’s get the F.B.I.
to put his picture
on the nightly news.

33:16.412 --> 33:18.368
See if the public
can identify him.

33:18.497 --> 33:21.079
Pretty cool.
Well done.

33:29.842 --> 33:33.505
I saw my face on the news.
I turned myself in.

33:33.596 --> 33:35.678
I did not kill Jess.

33:35.764 --> 33:38.016
- That girl meant the world to me.
— What was it, Willis?

33:38.100 --> 33:41.012
Did you end up buying
a night or two with her
and end up falling in love?

33:41.103 --> 33:45.312
No, no. You have it all
really, really wrong.

33:45.399 --> 33:47.560
Okay, why don’t you tell me
how it really, really is.

33:47.651 --> 33:50.188
Jess was my niece.

33:50.279 --> 33:52.144
Ah, you know, you’re not
starting off too good.

33:52.281 --> 33:56.320
See, Jessica Pearson
has no family members.
Not by blood.

33:56.410 --> 34:00.073
Jessica’s father and I
were best friends
since we were seven years old.

34:01.290 --> 34:03.201
When he died,

34:03.292 --> 34:06.750
I promised him that I would
take care of his daughter.
That was 10 years ago.

34:06.837 --> 34:08.452
And why should I believe you?

34:08.547 --> 34:11.755
I got photos of me and Jess
since she was five.

34:11.842 --> 34:13.252
Okay?

34:13.344 --> 34:15.801
Look. High school graduation.

34:15.888 --> 34:18.925
Afterthat, I paid
for two years of college.

34:19.016 --> 34:20.756
You—You can check it all out.

34:20.851 --> 34:25.436
As Jess got older,
she didn’t need me as much.

34:25.522 --> 34:28.605
Maybe I reminded her of her dad.
I don’t know.

34:30.194 --> 34:35.154
She calls me out of the blue
about some guy
who was scaring her.

34:36.575 --> 34:39.032
— The butcher?
— I took care of that.

34:39.119 --> 34:40.859
But I’m not stupid.

34:40.955 --> 34:44.539
I have eyes.
I saw how Jess’s life was going.

34:44.625 --> 34:48.117
— So you figured out
that she was—
- Yeah. I saw it.

34:48.212 --> 34:52.581
— So you followed her?
— I heard her scream.

34:52.675 --> 34:56.759
— So I kicked down the door—
— And you stuffed her client
in the closet.

34:56.845 --> 35:02.431
I came this close to killing him.
This close.

35:02.518 --> 35:06.136
You and me could be
sitting here now,
only you’d be right.

35:06.230 --> 35:08.186
Agent Booth,

35:08.274 --> 35:13.234
you got anybody
that you’re responsible for,

35:13.320 --> 35:18.030
who needs help even though
they feel like they got to be
out in the world on their own?

35:19.368 --> 35:20.983
Oh, yeah.

35:22.162 --> 35:23.572
Look, I’m in banking.

35:23.664 --> 35:25.620
I’m not a big guy.
I’m a medium guy.

35:25.708 --> 35:30.748
But I told Jess
that I could get investors
for her applesauce company...

35:30.838 --> 35:32.749
so that she could stop...

35:34.633 --> 35:37.045
taking clients for money
and make a go of it.

35:37.136 --> 35:38.546
Was she gonna
take the deal?

35:40.180 --> 35:42.341
She said she’d think about it.

35:43.976 --> 35:45.841
And that was
the last night
you saw her.

35:46.729 --> 35:48.560
Yes.

35:56.613 --> 36:01.653
Okay, so this is a rundown
of how the injuries were
dispersed across the remains.

36:01.744 --> 36:03.359
Four incisions to the skull,

36:03.454 --> 36:05.866
seven to the right arm,
six to the left,

36:05.956 --> 36:07.457
eight to the thoracic region,

36:07.541 --> 36:10.248
two to the pelvis
and another four on each leg.

36:10.336 --> 36:14.625
It appears as if the spacing
between the incisions
on the left arm...

36:14.715 --> 36:19.584
is equal to the spacing
between the incisions
on the thoracic region.

36:23.724 --> 36:27.091
Okay, that’s interesting.
Okay, let me try the right arm.

36:28.771 --> 36:31.638
Hmm.
Try the legs, Angela.

36:33.609 --> 36:35.725
Whoa. What is this telling us?

36:35.819 --> 36:38.401
This is the position
the victim was in
when her flesh was removed.

36:38.489 --> 36:40.525
She was protecting herself.

36:40.616 --> 36:43.403
She was cut 18 times
with surgical—like precision.

36:43.494 --> 36:46.486
Why would she stay
in the same position
throughout the entire attack?

36:46.580 --> 36:48.946
Perhaps she was already dead
at this point?

36:49.041 --> 36:51.032
Or worse,
she could have been paralyzed...

36:51.126 --> 36:54.618
and forced to bare witness
to the systematic carving
of her own flesh.

36:54.713 --> 36:56.920
There’s something very odd here.

36:57.007 --> 36:59.464
Yeah. But you’re
gonna have to be a little
more specific than that...

36:59.551 --> 37:02.509
for those of us who find
this entire scenario odd.

37:02.596 --> 37:05.554
These wounds are too regular,
too precise.

37:05.641 --> 37:07.097
Each one is calculated.

37:07.184 --> 37:11.018
The surgical precision,
the working knowledge
of the human anatomy—

37:11.146 --> 37:13.398
I think the doctor’s our guy.
[ Brennan ]
No.

37:13.482 --> 37:17.350
The evidence indicates
that this was done
by some kind of machine.

37:26.412 --> 37:29.154
Yeah, I believe
if Jessica Pearson
wanted to sell out,

37:29.248 --> 37:31.034
her partner might have been
angry enough to murder.

37:31.125 --> 37:32.615
Come on, really?
Over applesauce?

37:32.709 --> 37:34.415
For artisans,
it’s their life.

37:34.503 --> 37:36.744
You know,
Brooke might have thought
that Jessica was...

37:36.839 --> 37:39.000
attacking the very foundation
of her life.

37:39.091 --> 37:43.050
— Oh, better her partner is
a prostitute than sells out?
— Essentially, yeah.

37:43.137 --> 37:44.547
It’s not about money
for these people.

37:44.680 --> 37:46.716
[ Groans ]
You know, artisans
go into business...

37:46.807 --> 37:48.763
’cause they’re passionate
about the products they create.

37:48.851 --> 37:51.433
That is so un—American.
[ Scoffs ]

37:51.520 --> 37:54.227
Hey, so, uh—
I’m gonna move
out of the house tonight.

37:54.356 --> 37:56.221
Hey, you found a place.
You’ve been great,

37:56.316 --> 37:59.023
but I think we both know
it’s time I face
the world on my own.

37:59.111 --> 38:00.396
[Whispers ]
It’s time.

38:10.205 --> 38:13.493
Excuse me. Brooke Guminski,
we have a search warrant here
for the premises.

38:13.584 --> 38:16.576
Can’t this wait?
I’ve got orders to fill,
and I’m all by myself.

38:16.670 --> 38:19.207
Well, you should have considered
that before you killed Jessica.

38:19.298 --> 38:22.131
We know Jessica came
to visit you before she left
for Baltimore.

38:22.217 --> 38:25.209
- We know what you two were talking about.
— We didn’t talk about anything.

38:25.304 --> 38:27.636
She stopped by to grab a couple jars
before she left town.

38:27.764 --> 38:28.970
Booth?
Yep?

38:29.057 --> 38:30.718
I believe I discovered
the murder weapon.

38:30.809 --> 38:32.640
— What do we have here?
- Nothing.

38:32.728 --> 38:35.891
It’s a ribbon blender.
We use it to blend spices
into our sauce.

38:35.981 --> 38:39.269
Ifthe victim fell into this blender
while the blades were spinning,

38:39.359 --> 38:42.817
her body would have become
wedged to the side...

38:42.905 --> 38:45.521
where the blades would have
continuously sliced her...

38:45.616 --> 38:48.278
at a 45—degree angle
while removing her flesh.

38:49.203 --> 38:50.818
It was an accident, wasn’t it?

38:50.913 --> 38:53.245
[ Sniffles ]

38:53.332 --> 38:57.621
- Bones?
— We are certain to find bone
shards or splinters in here.

38:57.711 --> 39:00.999
Look, it looks much better
to the jury if you tell me
that it was an accident...

39:01.089 --> 39:03.626
before Bones here
finds any evidence.

39:07.721 --> 39:10.087
It was an accident.

39:10.182 --> 39:13.891
She told me she wanted to sell,
and I slapped her and—
[ Sniffles ]

39:17.356 --> 39:19.813
Would it have been so bad
to make some money?

39:19.900 --> 39:23.643
My parents only cared about money.
It destroyed their marriage.

39:23.737 --> 39:25.443
It destroyed my childhood.

39:25.531 --> 39:28.113
I didn’t mean for Jessica
to fall in.

39:28.200 --> 39:30.316
I turned it off,
but it was too late.

39:31.620 --> 39:34.202
I didn’t know what to do,
so I cleaned up the mess...

39:34.289 --> 39:35.790
and I dumped the body
down the street.

39:38.001 --> 39:40.617
I’m sorry.

39:43.966 --> 39:46.799
[Crying I

39:46.885 --> 39:48.386
[ Sniffles ]

40:06.530 --> 40:10.398
Sometimes I feel guilty
feeling so good
after Christine goes to bed.

40:10.492 --> 40:13.234
It’s good to be happy
when the baby goes down.

40:13.370 --> 40:16.453
Is it?
Yeah, it is. It gives us
time to be alone, huh?

40:16.582 --> 40:17.992
This applesauce
is pretty good.
[ Chuckles ]

40:18.125 --> 40:20.741
Yeah. You want some?
No. The wine is fine.

40:20.836 --> 40:23.748
It’s not bad,
I’m telling you.
Nine bucks.

40:23.839 --> 40:27.627
A nine-buck applesauce
is kind of like
drinking a fine wine.

40:27.759 --> 40:30.045
[Both Laugh]
I mean,
I’m telling you.

40:30.137 --> 40:31.627
Plus, keeps the doctor away.

40:31.722 --> 40:34.885
Actually, eating too many apples
could do the opposite,

40:34.975 --> 40:37.808
since they contain
a lot of sugar.

40:37.894 --> 40:39.395
You could get diabetes.

40:40.314 --> 40:41.770
Great.

40:41.857 --> 40:45.065
That’s nine bucks
down the drain, hmm?
You know what?

40:45.193 --> 40:47.104
Stick with the scotch.
[ Chuckles ]

40:47.195 --> 40:48.355
Alone time.
Right.

40:50.115 --> 40:52.527
— All right, thanks.
— What? Wait. You’re leaving?

40:52.618 --> 40:55.200
Yeah, I don’t want
to overstay my welcome.
Thanks a million though for—

40:55.287 --> 40:58.700
Come on, Sweets.
Come on in. You know,
hey, have some sauce.

40:58.790 --> 41:02.408
We have apple or wine.
But you can’t have my scotch.

41:02.502 --> 41:05.244
Uh, did I somehow
give you the impression
that you should leave?

41:05.339 --> 41:07.830
Because you haven’t
overstayed your welcome yet.

41:07.924 --> 41:10.210
Come on, put the bag back.
Put it back.

41:10.302 --> 41:13.669
— Is this because you want
to win the pool?
— Oh, you know about that?

41:13.764 --> 41:17.302
Yeah, Booth only wins if I stay
another two weeks, right?

41:17.392 --> 41:19.929
— Is that why
you want him to stay?
— No. No.

41:20.020 --> 41:22.932
Don’t you think that as a man,
I should be on my own?
I mean—

41:23.023 --> 41:24.479
Most cultures
have ceremonies...

41:24.608 --> 41:27.099
to celebrate milestones
in a man’s life.
[ Booth ] Oh.

41:27.194 --> 41:28.684
Oh, God, this isn’t about
circumcision, is it?

41:28.820 --> 41:30.401
No, it’s about dancing.
What?

41:30.489 --> 41:34.528
There are three important
elements in moving on
past an old relationship.

41:34.618 --> 41:36.950
- Admission.
- I admit it’s over with Daisy.

41:37.037 --> 41:39.073
— Cleansing.
- Right. You were in ourjet tub.

41:39.206 --> 41:43.620
— And celebration.
— So I can’t get my own apartment
till I celebrate being alone?

41:43.710 --> 41:45.541
